data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Opulent and ageless; this is a highly desirable West of Trail home location. Embrace the beauty of this spacious custom style pool home, updated in 2003. A covered foyer with double entry doors opens into a large formal living room with French doors and a view of a private 384 square foot in ground pool, and outdoor kitchen, under an elevated large screened enclosure.  The split bedroom floor plan features a ground level master suite, with an adjacent bonus office/nursery room. The formal living room and formal dining room are diagonally across from each other and the open plan, windows, and high ceilings throughout this home create expansive volume and space throughout. The hallway leads to the eat-in kitchen which has a large bar area that opens to the great room which has two sky lights, and a wood burning fireplace.  A pocket door entry off of the great room leads to a hallway with two additional bedrooms, a utility/laundry room with a closet and window, and a shared large pool bath with shower. Off of the kitchen and tucked away near the stairs, there is a powder room. The staircase, with entry access near the interior garage door leads to a separate second floor master bedroom suite with a kitchenette, and a full bath. The highlights of this property include a highly desirable location within two blocks to Sarasota Bay, close proximity to Southside Village, Southside Elementary School and Sarasota Memorial Hospital. New concrete tile roof in 2016, and a new 16 seer heat pump A/C installed in 2022. The kitchen and bathrooms have granite countertops. The kitchen has stainless steel appliances and a wet bar. There are minor maintenance items that Buyer will want to address after closing. Property is being sold “As Is”.
